QUALITY_MEASURE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Class> QUALITY_MEASURE

QUALITY_DEFAULT_VALUE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Double> QUALITY_DEFAULT_VALUE
The default return value of a distance function that can be used if for some reason a distance cannot be computed.

QUALITY_N_METRIC_ROOT

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Double> QUALITY_N_METRIC_ROOT
The root parameter in the distance function: in case of the n-norm this is at the same time also the exponent. For instance, the EuclideanDistance distance has a root value of two, whereas the ManhattanDistance norm has a root of one. In the RelativeSquaredError, the default root is also two, but this value may be changed.

QUALITY_MEASURES

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup QUALITY_MEASURES
Here you can specify how to evaluate the quality of a parameter set with respect to given experimental data.

ODE_SOLVER

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Class> ODE_SOLVER
This gives the class name of the default solver for ordinary differential equation systems. The associated class must implement AbstractDESSolver and must have a constructor without any parameters.

SIM_END_TIME

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Double> SIM_END_TIME
With the associated non-negative double number that has to be greater than 0 when simulating SBML models, it is possible to perform a simulation.

SIM_START_TIME

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Double> SIM_START_TIME
The double value associated with this key must, in case of SBML equal to zero. Generally, any start time would be possible. This is why this key exists. But SBML is defined to start its simulation at the time zero.

SIM_STEP_SIZE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Double> SIM_STEP_SIZE
The greater this value the longer the computation time, but the more accurate will be the result.

SIMULATION_CONFIGURATION

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup SIMULATION_CONFIGURATION
Parameters for the simulation
